places.name: Finest At Sea
places.address: Finest At Sea, 4675 Arbutus St, Vancouver, BC V6J 4A3

featured_reviews.review_id: I stopped in to check out the smoked salmon offerings. Top quality product and a variety of options available. I decided to have fish and chips while I was there. I had a piece of halibut. It was everything I want a piece of battered fish to be. Crispy batter, tender, flaky fish. Excellent fries and tartar sauce. The coleslaw was adequate, but not a show stopper. It's worth a trip, for sure!

featured_reviews.review_id:
Great store with more than just seafood items. In a pinch, you could come in and pick up dry pasta, fresh fruits and veg , and of course seafood.

I normally come here in the summer for salmon and when the time is right spot prawns and they don't disappoint.

A lot of traffic (as you can see from the other posts) are mostly commenting on fish and chips and their other cooked food. Again, it's just a portion of what they do.

The fish and chips are solid and the batter is not too thick. Got takeout and ate it 20 minutes later and was still crispy. Recommend calling the order in , especially if it's getting close to lunch time as there is a high school close by and it can get crowded. People talk about the fries and they are good. For value and quantity, it definitely hits the spot. Also tried the curries eggplant halibut wrap. It was good. Maybe a bit mild for my tastes but for those wanting that light curry flavour with their fish, this would work for you.

Parking in the complex , with the highschool crowd etc...can be a bit of a slog depending on the time. Though I find the best and easiest place to park is on the street.

featured_reviews.review_id:
After visiting their Victoria location last year, I was keen to go the Vancouver Location in Arbutus for having fish and chips. The fish was delicious, crispy and fresh as expected. We tried sockeye salmon fish, with potato fries, coleslaw salad. We also had the yummy bisque for the first time (a thick seafood fish soup ) with some garlic bread.
The prices were very reasonable. Great portion size. The fish and chips dinner is enough for teo people. I will visit this place again for trying the other fish cuisines.

featured_reviews.review_id: Hands down, best fish and chips I've ever had in my life. We got the halibut and chips - fish tasted so fresh, was flaky in the inside and had a great exterior crunch. I must say though, the chips (i.e. fries), was the star of the dish for me - they were cooked to perfection. Crunchy on the outside and fluffy on the inside, every single one of them. Service was quick and the patio atmosphere with a good view just makes this place that much better. It's about a 5min walk from Granville Island. 10000000% would recommend this place to anyone that loves good food.

featured_reviews.review_id:
To be concise.. yes, I would recommend.

Pro: delicious. Good portions. Very friendly staff (exceptional customer service)

Con: parking is difficult. No indoor or covered seating.

We tried the Cod fish and chips. Excellent batter and the fries were delicious. Tatar sauce was rich and satisfying. Coleslaw was underwhelming and slightly boring.

We also had the Oyster "Po Boy" sandwich. The flavour was amazing and unique. Highly recommend.

Overall, great service and exciting sandwich menu. Fish and chips were above par. I wished there were some covered seating as you're completely exposed to the elements.

Of note: walking distance to Granville Island! Also, expect to wait to be served during peak hours.

featured_reviews.review_id:
Was running errand in the area. We actually waited over 30 minutes for them to open, it was well worth it!

We got 3pcs snapper fish&chips! Good portion! The batter was crispy, fish was moist, perfectly seasoned! It was soooooo good, really hit the spot! Tartar sauce was light and refreshing, not heavy at all. I craved this again 3-4 times that same day, I'm still thinking about it today!

We also got the scallop, grilled, over rice, with garlic butter! Scallop was also perfectly cooked! Sweet and juicy! I enjoyed dipping the scallop in the butter and adding tartar sauce to the rice for the perfect bite!

Food was a little slow but we went right when they open so it was understandable. I appreciate that the chef take his time to prepare the food properly instead of rushing them out.

Service was friendly and casual, very warm and welcoming! We enjoyed our conversation with them and our time there. This was also the first time we took our puppy to a restaurant, we were glad it was a pleasant experience.

Their supplies came late that day and we couldn't order what we originally wanted, but we would definitely be back for other dishes. What we ended up ordering turn out great though, so no complain there! But next time we want to try cod fish& chips, grilled calamari, and clam chowder. :)

We wish they have deep fried oysters too, I think it will be amazing!

featured_reviews.review_id: Fish Cafe was great! I'm from Toronto and my cousin mentioned BC has great seafood, it's fresh. We started with the grilled calamari with garlic butter which was a great combo. I had a Greek salad with 1pc fish and chips. He had the grilled salmon on rice. For dessert we tried their chocolate cake (they didn't have anymore carrot cake). It's understandable that some menu items wouldn't be available due to the freshness of the food so we didn't get a chance to try their crab cakes or clam chowder. I would highly recommend the fish and chips, the snapper was very light and battered perfectly. Overall I'm happy we visited and I would definitely go back if I visit BC again :)

A small favour ~ It would be nice to have the option of different types of Buns, besides a White Bun ~ thank you!

This year we were late for canning Sockeye salmon.  After phoning several places and not having any success we stumbled on to 7 seas.

Spoke with Stevie who said yes they had Sockeye. The price was quite reasonable.

We got our Salmon. They dressed, cleaned and cut off the fins - ready for canning.

featured_reviews.review_id: A great unassuming fish and chips place that my husband and I happened to come across. The interior is pretty basic and nothing to write home about, but the food was delicious and service quick. I got the halibut which was fried to perfection - crisp on the outside, juicy on the inside. The fries and coleslaw were also fantastic though I would've liked a bit more slaw because it was so good. Husband got the regular fish (we're assuming cod) which was also delicious and cheaper than halibut. He got the chowder with his combo which lacked salt but was an easy fix and would be good for those trying to be mindful of their salt intake. We were the only customers for a while on a Tuesday at lunch so you wouldn't have to wait long if you're in a rush. We will definitely be back!

featured_reviews.review_id:
Stopped in for Happy Hour (3pm-5pm daily) and the food, service, and vibe were all spot on!

First, our server was Norm and he was great! Personable and funny and checked in the perfect amount of times. He's the type of server that elevates your dining experience. I applaud the entire staff as their communication was great and they all worked together to handle a packed house very efficiently.

Now onto the food. We did the Crispy Calamari, Truffle Parmesan Fries, Miso Glazed Short Ribs, and Joe's Chilled Seafood Platter. We closed it out with the Creme Brulee.

The calamari was the best I've ever had. We ended out grabbing a 2nd order of those. Fries were tasty. The short ribs were so-so. Our favorites on the seafood platter were the scallop ceviche and the albacore tuna crudo. The prawns were some big boys as well. All of the seafood tasted fresh and the platter had great plating.

The creme brulee was presented well and took a couple of hits to crack through the top which is expected. Amazing!

Overall, the food quality, price point, and service puts this place at 5 stars for me.

featured_reviews.review_id:
Amazing food at very reasonable prices during happy hour lunch service. Staff were friendly and very attentive. Food came out very quick so kudos to the back of the house for keeping things moving during happy hour!

We got lobster rolls, truffle fries, fish tacos, and 2 of each regular oyster and premium oyster.
For drinks we ordered their red sangria (rotating basis presumably between red and white wines) and a non-alcoholic local hazy IPA. We aren't big drinkers so won't go into detail, nevertheless they were both refreshing and tasty drinks that paired well with our food choices.

The lobster roll was great, you can taste the freshness of the lobster meat itself. This was something we did not find in the lobsters we've personally had around Toronto. The dressing and small cuts of veggies did well to complement and complete the lobster roll.

Truffle fries were well seasoned, being able to get hints of truffle (presumably from truffle oil) every other bite or so. The aioli paired well with the fries as well.

Fish tacos were fresh, the flavor and texture of the coleslaw went well to balance out the grease of a fried fish fillet. I probably could have gone for another order but didn't want to risk a permanent food coma.

One set of oysters tasted more of the ocean than the other. Going by what the wait staff pointed out as the regular vs premium, the latter had the more ocean-y briney taste. Not for everyone especially if you aren't a fan of seafood, but if you dabble then these are definitely worth a try at a reasonable price.

All in all, we were thoroughly impressed with all aspects of our visit. It is on our very short list of places we'd definitely revisit on our next stop in Vancouver!

We got lobster rolls, truffle fries, fish tacos, and 2 of each regular oyster and premium oyster.
For drinks we ordered their red sangria (rotating basis presumably between red and white wines) and a non-alcoholic local hazy IPA. We aren't big drinkers so won't go into detail, nevertheless they were both refreshing and tasty drinks that paired well with our food choices.

The lobster roll was great, you can taste the freshness of the lobster meat itself. This was something we did not find in the lobsters we've personally had around Toronto. The dressing and small cuts of veggies did well to complement and complete the lobster roll.

Truffle fries were well seasoned, being able to get hints of truffle (presumably from truffle oil) every other bite or so. The aioli paired well with the fries as well.

Fish tacos were fresh, the flavor and texture of the coleslaw went well to balance out the grease of a fried fish fillet. I probably could have gone for another order but didn't want to risk a permanent food coma.

One set of oysters tasted more of the ocean than the other. Going by what the wait staff pointed out as the regular vs premium, the latter had the more ocean-y briney taste. Not for everyone especially if you aren't a fan of seafood, but if you dabble then these are definitely worth a try at a reasonable price.

All in all, we were thoroughly impressed with all aspects of our visit. It is on our very short list of places we'd definitely revisit on our next stop in Vancouver!

featured_reviews.review_id: Amazing oysters, and very reasonable happy hour specials. The tuna tartare was delicious as well, and the lobster poutine was good but had very little lobster. Thankfully the waitress kindly took it off of our bill. I will always return for the delicious oysters

featured_reviews.review_id:
This place is in the top 3 of best oysters I've ever had! And the #1 spot for the best uni (sea urchin) I've ever eaten. Definitely a 5 star!

Let's break down this joint. Great vibin atmosphere. We were seated exactly at our reservation time. Our server was nice, quick, and knowledgeable on the menu. She mentioned the uni was firm and that made me go for it (I've had some bad experiences with this delicacy). It was delicious.

Ordered many different dishes - Sun Seeker, Sweet Select, and Kumamoto oysters were all delicious and fresh. One of them were very meaty. The horseradish is freshly grated. Lobster poutine was packed with lobster but pretty meh overall. Crab cake was a bit dry. 6pc scallop was seared to perfection. The tuna tartare was a bit salty, but still tasted good. The octopus was amazing and tender. And of course as mentioned earlier, the uni was the best and most fresh I've ever had.

The wife says they make an amazing espresso martini. Definitely get a reservation as this spot was packed on a Monday night. They have fresh oysters that you can take home if you like to shuck (who doesn't like to shuck)? When I visit Vancouver again, I will definitely be stopping by.

places.name: New Fishport Seafood Bistro
places.address: New Fishport Seafood Bistro, 620 SE Marine Dr, Vancouver, BC V5X 2T4

featured_reviews.review_id:
The owner and chef used to work at Dynasty Chinese Restaurant before they moved out to their own place.

The food has good "wok" flavour, uses fresh ingredients, is tasty and better if you speak Cantonese so you can get the daily specials and seafood of the day, that aren't listed in the menu.

We came for a group dinner and the portions were generous. Some dishes were a bit oily.

My favourite was their fish maw baked with running chicken - the flavours were very complementary and the fish maw was cooked just right.

The restaurant isn't that nice looking; decor is simple and a bit dated, with tables fairly placed close together. They have two private rooms. It has a little bit of a hole-in-the-wall feeling but prices certainly were at par if not even more expensive than other restaurants with much nicer decor.

Worth it to come back for the food, but not necessarily to present to visitors given the overall ambiance and dining experience.

featured_reviews.review_id:
Our first time trying New Fishport Seafood Bistro was actually take out last year but we finally managed to visit in person a few weeks ago. It's located in a rather non-descript mini mall on Marine.

The interior isn't huge and they sat us at one of the few small tables in the restaurant. We ordered the Mixed Vegetables, Mui Choy Kau Yuk,
House Special Fried Rice, and we wanted to order a crab dish. They tried to convince us that we ordered too much... As it turns out, they mistakenly gave us the wrong crab dish. We ordered a simple ginger and green onion crab but they wound up giving us their special Fire Crab with Sticky Rice. The reason why they call it that is because they pour some liquid on the sticky rice and set it on fire tableside. While it wasn't what we ordered, it turned out pretty good with a spicy garlic soy flavour.

Service was pretty good and food was tasty. Ended the meal with a taro tapioca dessert.

featured_reviews.review_id: Food was about average for a Cantonese seafood restaurant but the prices were quite a bit higher than the standard. For the quality of food itself it's actually not bad but it's about the full dining experience and to be honest I felt like my table received significantly worse service than other tables. Most likely based on the dishes we ordered. I mean our food was by no means "cheap" but we did not purchase any of those recommendations the server told us about that costs way more money.  We even over heard one of the servers ( or owner ) saying to another worker that they were relieved we were finally leaving. Probably because we were not spending "that much" for dinner.... And could finally fill our table with other people. No I will never set foot in this restaurant again or any future establishments the owner  opens in the future.  By no means is this review meant to defame the restaurant, maybe they were just feeling too stressed from the covid restrictions and really needed the money.  but to be treated based on how much we are willing to spend on a meal simply is a first... oh and y'all wondering how much the meal cost, it was a little over $300 with 12% tips ( why did I tip? Because it's not the servers faults they give that kind of service, more likely how the owner teaches the servers how to serve higher value customers)

places.description: Casual kitchen dishing up oysters, fish 'n' chips & more, along with British Columbia beers/wines.
places.address: Tony's Fish & Oyster Cafe, 1511 Anderson St, Vancouver, BC V6H 3R5

featured_reviews.review_id: My partner suggested this spot after reading some reviews online, it's a small family friendly joint! The restaurant gets quite busy during lunch, I would suggest plan accordingly and come after the lunch rush. The restaurant holds about 20 people or less, the ambiance is that of a fish spot with seafood art on the walls. Since this was our first stop in Granville Island and wanted to try and see everything, we decided to share the clam chowder and the infamous fish and Chips! Great customer service, daughter was our server, mother washing dishes very humble people. If you are in a hurry, I wouldn't suggest coming here, everything is made fresh to order so it'll take a min. The food was hot and absolutely delicious, one of the best fish and chips around!

featured_reviews.review_id:
Took the family out to this establishment for lunch today. Tony's Fish & Oyster Cafe proved to be a delightful culinary escapade for seafood enthusiasts like myself. The restaurant's inviting ambiance and friendly staff immediately set the stage for a memorable dining experience. With a diverse menu boasting a variety of seafood delicacies, our taste buds were in for a treat.

To start, we ordered the Caesar Salad, and it was a refreshing and well-balanced dish. The crisp romaine lettuce was generously coated in a tangy dressing, complemented by a sprinkle of Parmesan cheese and crunchy croutons. It served as an excellent precursor to the seafood feast that awaited us.  I will note a pretty standard caesar salad.

Next up was the Seafood Sampler, a delightful platter brimming with ocean treasures. The array of Seafood Clams, Mussels, Prawns and Scallops with breaded Oysters and deep fried Cod was impeccably fresh and expertly prepared. The sampler was a great way to explore various flavours of the sea in one dish.

The Clam Chowder was a standout among the starters. Creamy, rich, and generously loaded with tender clams, it warmed our souls and left us craving more. The balance of flavours was spot on, and the hearty portion made it perfect for sharing.

Moving on to the Prawn Appetizer, we were delighted by the succulent prawns cooked to perfection. The dish was accented with a zesty marinade that enhanced the natural sweetness of the prawns. It was an appetizer we couldn't resist finishing entirely, even though we knew we had a main course to savour.

The highlight of the meal was undoubtedly the Cioppino, a seafood stew packed with an array of fish, mussels, and squid. The broth was a harmonious symphony of tomatoes, garlic, and herbs that danced on our palates with every spoonful. The seafood was tender, indicating the use of fresh catch, and the dish was served piping hot, adding to its comforting appeal. Although it may seem simple, this dish showcased Tony's expertise in crafting seafood classics.

Overall, Tony's Fish & Oyster Cafe earns a solid 4-star rating. The dining experience was enhanced not only by the delectable seafood offerings but also by the warm and attentive service provided by the sever. While some dishes stood out more than others, the restaurant's commitment to quality and flavoursome seafood left a lasting impression on our taste buds. Tony's Fish & Oyster Cafe is a worthy destination to satisfy your cravings.

featured_reviews.response_from_owner_text:
Hello,

 We are so sorry about the poor experience  you had at our store. We greatly appreciate your feed back, we have lots of part time and new staff and you've brought a weakness in our business to our attention that we can now work on.

We keep all our harvest tags right beside the bin we sell our shellfish out of so I am surprised that staff on site yesterday could not find them as they all know where they are, we will talk to them about this.


As for our oyster the kusshi we have in stock were harvested Oct 19th/23. The malpeque and beausoleil  were harvested on the 15th and 18th respectively.

Please reach out via email orders@dailycatchseafood.ca , we would love to make it up to the both of you!

warm regards,

I recently had the opportunity to visit Daily Catch, a retail seafood shop that I had heard great things about. From the moment I walked in, I was impressed with the friendly and attentive customer service I received from the staff. They were more than happy to answer any questions I had about the products and make recommendations based on my preferences.

The seafood at Daily Catch is absolutely top-notch. The freshness and quality of the seafood they sell is outstanding. They had variety of species to choose from and were all expertly handled and packaged. I especially enjoyed the local oysters and the fresh sashimi-grade tuna. The prices were very reasonable, and they had good deals on the specials of the day.

I also appreciated the shop's commitment to sourcing sustainable seafood. It's always good to know that the seafood I'm purchasing is not only delicious but also responsibly sourced.

featured_reviews.response_from_owner_text:
Hello Saida, 
Sorry you had such a poor experience at our store. When the staff were asked about the situation, the one helping you, thought you had asked "If the fish was Cut Today" and because it was he replied "yes". When you asked him "if it was previously frozen" he replied "it was" not because he was changing his mind or lying earlier but because in his mind he wasn't asked if it was fresh or frozen yet. The staff who was helping you has worked for us for a long time and knows that the salmon right now is not fresh, there is no incentive for him to lie about it so I honestly believe this is a miss communication on our part. Occasionally staff might miss-hear what a customer is saying, we serve thousands of customers a week so its bound to happen every once in a while. 
 We are extremely transparent about our products. We don't hide the fact that this time of year we sell previously frozen wild Salmon as there is no fresh wild pacific salmon available for commercial purposes for several more months. All Wild Salmon being sold outside of Fresh Season is always going to be previously frozen, unless it is farmed. Our store Signage is also usually very accurate and products that are Fresh will say so. The more transparent we are the better business we become. Our employees have no incentive lying about our products it would only get them in trouble if done in anyway that isn't an honest mistake. For this reason and the employee in questions vast knowledge on our products I believe this was an honest mistake.
 As for the frozen Salmon its by far the highest quality Sockeye you can purchase outside of fresh season. We pay a lot more for it so that we can sell it with a smile knowing the quality is superb, we can guarantee you will enjoy it!
 We would love to here more from you as well as refund your purchase, Please Email us at Orders@dailycatchseafood.ca so we can connect, Thank You

Came with a group of 7 on a chilly night for a special dinner. It was a busy Friday night. First the good, the food was better than I remembered it being. Everything was very flavourful and well presented, the was perfectly cooked (previously I'd been served Sable fish that was raw in the middle).

What wasn't great was the service, yes it was a busy night and our server was trying to be present but it seemed obvious he was rushed when he did check in, combined with a long pause between appys and dinner, then another long pause before we were asked about desert then our coffees didn't come till after we were done with desert. Although the bill managed to show up well before we were done. At this point the restaurant was not busy.

Lastly our server managed to cut himself and put out plates for appys with blood smears on them and didn't.notice till I asked another server who very quickly swept them up. Appys arrived without replacement plates until it was pointed out. Not a good performance for premiere dining....

featured_reviews.review_id:
Went for dinner last night and was absolutely blown away by the service. While the food was amazing, the service was incomparable! My friends and I had the pleasure of dining with Tara and her colleagues and this was by far my best dining experience in the city (and I'm a local)!

Tara was knowledgeable, attentive and just a pleasure to be around. From the moment we arrived we were warmly greeted and never once did we have to try and seek her attention as she was always checking in. Any time someone left the table, her and her team were quick ensure settings and napkins remained tidy and presentable upon our arrival back. Tara explained the menu in detail and was quick to recommend food and beverage pairings that we were all pleased with. The food was beautifully presented, tasted great and everyone was satisfied.

While I don't have photos of everything we ordered, the raw oysters were fresh and sweet, prawns were plump and juicy, and sashimi was fresh and paired with an in house soy sauce. I ordered the beef tenderloin and asked for it to be cooked between medium rare and rare and it was cooked to perfection. It was tender, seared crisp on the outside and juicy on the inside. I also ordered the truffle fries as a side and will say you have to try them!

Tara is a gem and I want to thank her and the staff for creating such a welcoming atmosphere that was paired with amazing food! I don't know how it took me so long to come here but can definitely say I will be back.

Make your reservation now and thank me later!

featured_reviews.review_id: Came here last night for my one year anniversary with my partners. The place was very accommodating about letting us move our reservation up a bit from when we originally set it. The place is very beautiful, well decorated and very elegant yet cozy. We sat on the enclosed patio and the temperature was perfect, not to mention the ivy covered lanterns giving soft romantic light to the room. We were given a hand written congratulations from the restaurant, which was a very sweet personal touch. Our server, Phillip, was engaging, charming, and was very well versed on the menu. Any question he couldn't answer he was quick to ask the kitchen. He also checked in with us all night and was constantly refilling our waters. It was a very royal treatment we did not expect at that price point, for certain. We got the two tier seafood platter, the scallops entre, and a beef tenderloin to split. Not only were they very attentive to my dairy allergy, and my wife's peanut allergy, but everything we tried exceeded our expectations. Never had jellyfish before here and I would for certain try it again. The oysters were fresh and absolutely something I was excited for as an oyster lover, I was not disappointed. In terms of accessibility I'd say very for a wheelchair, but I was having a good day so walked in with my cane. The parking is subject to downtown and I didn't see a disabled spot, but that doesn't mean they aren't there. Likely just filled before we got there. However they do offer valet services. They are very accommodating if you call ahead. Definitely recommend this place to seafood lovers looking for a nice elegant date spot.

featured_reviews.review_id:
Came for dinner on a Sunday. It was pretty empty so I don't think there's a need for reservations unless you want to reserve a particular dish like we did.

The highlight of the night was definitely the pigeon, the melon soup and the sweet and sour pork.

The pigeon was really crispy and juicy at the same time. Perfectly salted and delicious (no Pic as it was grabbed at quickly)

The melon soup was so full of goods that I don't think it should be called a soup and instead it should be considered a meal. There was craband scallops inside. The soup was so sweet not in a fake sugary kind of way but a savory and seafood kind of way. Would recommend if money is of no object

The sweet and sour pork was surprisingly good. Crispy on the outside. Perfect balance of sweet and salty. The meat wasn't dry but instead very crisp in a good way.

Overall the food here was pretty good. Not overly salty and didn't make me drink loads of water afterwards. The service was friendly and fast. My dirty plates were switched out every time a shell landed on it. The prices are appropriate for the amount of food and quality of food. Would definitely recommend the pigeon and sweet and sour pork. The atmosphere was nice because only half the restaurant was full. People were well spaced out and lots of wait staff to help.

3 stars for dinner, 5 stars for dim sum. Average = 4 stars.

Dinner service was very short-staffed with the waiters yelling to be heard.

Asked for red vinegar 5 times and guess what? It never came. I can't eat Chinese food without it, soooo....yeah. Sad dinner. Also slow service at dinner meant we were there for 4 hours. O.m.g.

And the 2nd course of the Peking duck was forgotten until we reminded them an hour later.

featured_reviews.review_text:
3 stars for dinner, 5 stars for dim sum. Average = 4 stars.

Dinner service was very short-staffed with the waiters yelling to be heard.

Asked for red vinegar 5 times and guess what? It never came. I can't eat Chinese food without it, soooo....yeah. Sad dinner. Also slow service at dinner meant we were there for 4 hours. O.m.g.

And the 2nd course of the Peking duck was forgotten until we reminded them an hour later.

But - seafood was fresh,Peking duck crispy and light, veggies crisp, and sauces on point.

Garlic wings and roasted green peppers were a favorite.

4.5. Great spot with delicious food. The menu isn't huge but the features menu is sizable and almost as fulsome as the regular menu.
No meat - all fish options and a hearty mix of raw and cooked. Primarily raw fish appetizers but also some salads and veg dishes available. (The Burrata was the most expensive I've seen on a menu).
The apps were great- we saw almost every table around us get the French fries- they're delish also really enjoyed the yellow beans (heavy on the tarragon). The mains were good but they don't come with sides- nice to share some sides for the table.
Service was very friendly, drinks were good- the mocktails were fine, not amazing.
The atmosphere was great- big patio and the seating inside is also ample.
Many vegetarian options!

featured_reviews.review_text: Amazing food, everything I tried was delicious. Can't even pick a favorite item. Oysters, mussels, sable fish, salmon tasted all very fresh and prepared excellently.

featured_reviews.review_id: I'd been wanting to try this place for the last 5-10 years as I used to live nearby and always passed by. Finally just did so. The service is top notch. We had two very nice attentive waiters serving us. The atmosphere is lovely and lively, and the patio is pleasant. The food was very good but lacking the wow factor I was expecting, and my friend thought the same. I think part of the reason is, the bar is now set so high by all the good places to eat in this city. We had the mussels, halibut cheeks, hand cut fries and pea tips. The best mussels I've had still remains those at Locals restaurant in Courtenay. The best halibut cheeks my friend has had still remains at the now closed West restaurant in Vancouver. It was my first time trying halibut cheeks so I was quite excited, but they were somewhat bland and to me, the texture made it seem like it could have been from any part of the fish. They were served with tartar sauce and pickles which was interesting. Very small serving size for a $50 entree; not enough for one person if you're hungry. I filled up on fries and bread instead. My friend is a huge pea tips fan and as I predicted, he prefers the traditional Chinese method of cooking them, with more subtle flavouring and more garlic. I agree that method allows the bitterness and flavour of the pea tips to shine. But the soy sauce / sesame oil variation at Oddfish was still nice. In my opinion, the best part of the meal was the hand cut fries, the aioli it was served with, and the carbonated water made on their in-house machine. Very good carbonated water. All in all, I'd go back, but I wouldn't run back.

featured_reviews.review_id:
Fresh ingredients but portions are bit small.

Came here for our first dinner during our visit in Vancouver on a Friday night. The place was fully booked the only place available for us was in the heated patio area. The patio areas had plenty of heat lamps and the place was fully closed off so you won't need to worry about rain or snow (we were here during March and it actually snowed during our dinner!)

The food was pretty good, we ordered tiger shrimp cocktails, grilled oysters, assorted sashimi platter, seared scallops and a bowl of clams. Our favourite was the seared scallops hands down. We also orders some vegetable dish and they were amazing too! The beets with avocado and warm goat cheese was out of this world! The portion was kind of small so consider yourself warned. But the quality was certainly worthy of the price tag.

Would come back again!

featured_reviews.review_id:
We made a table reservation before we left the UK. This was our last meal in Vancouver before heading home.

Given that it was a Sunday when we visited, this place was fully booked and upon arrival, we could see why. It is located by the harbour and the views out are fabulous. We had a table outside as it was a pleasant evening.

Starters comprised of calamari and a Caesar salad, which we shared between us (the waiter plated up two half plates for us). For our mains we shared a seaside platter and a portion of truffle fries. We had 6 drinks over the course of the evening too.

As I mentioned our wedding anniversary upon booking, we were gifted a lovely cake for dessert.

Service was good given how busy they were. And the food was served hot and well presented.

Total bill with taxes and grats $220, PS132

featured_reviews.review_id: I brought my dog to Stanley Park for a walk today, and while passing by this unique-looking seafood restaurant with a harbor backdrop, I thought of buying some small dishes to take for a picnic. The restaurant's staff said they usually don't do takeout, but she offered to inquire for me. Shortly after, a person who appeared to be the manager came out with a smile and asked me, "What would you like to order?" I ordered two appetizers, Signature Wok Squid and Fried Oysters. He also suggested that I could get a portion of steamed rice or fried rice to go along with them.I sat on a chair by the harbor and started tasting a few bites. Both the squid and oyster were very fresh, and the squid had a great flavor. Paired with white rice, it was just right. The dipping sauce for the fried oyster had a hint of orange sweetness, and it was delicious. I definitely need to go back to the restaurant, sit on that beautiful patio, and enjoy another seafood meal.

featured_reviews.review_id: I love coming to Pink Peppercorn and it never disappoints! Every time I come i always rotate with the rack of lamb or the seafood pasta. The rack of lamb is always cooked to perfection and the mashed potatoes is to die for because it's not like any mashed potatoes I've ever had its sweet but savory at the same time. The portions are big plenty of veggies on the plate and presentation is always beautiful. The seafood pasta is so delish! I love the variety and amount of seafood that it comes with. Today my friend and I shared the mushroom soup. It was one of the features of the night and it was the best mushroom soup I've ever tasted! Rich, creamy and packed with flavor! I loved how the mushroom was blended but u can still taste the mushrooms and it had a nice garlic flavor. I wish it was a permanent item on the menu I'd take this mushroom soup over the clam chowder anytime! Our servers Arturo and Teddy bear both give great service with a great sense of humor! Hopefully next time I'll try something else off the menu!

I had to write a review after my family and I had a fantastic dinner last night at Pink Peppercorn. It is my brother's favourite place, but it has been a while for me since I no longer live nearby. Not only did the food exceed our expectations, so did the service.

I had the smoked sablefish, which was accompanied by a huge portion of veggies. It was a good portion, and super well plated. Others had the New York steak, cedar planked salmon, the salmon Wellington, and rack of lamb. Everyone was super happy with their meals. We also ordered the calamari starter, which was very fresh! The meal came with their complimentary warm bread and lobster oil, which was divine.

The star was our server. The lone man appeared to be working the entire restaurant alone. Serving, taking orders, and even bartending. He didn't skip a beat, and I was blown away. He deserves 5 stars and a big raise/bonus! Thank you for a wonderful evening,

featured_reviews.review_id:
Long ago, The Cannery restaurant was a family favourite. It sat on the waterfront, 2 kilometres west of the Ironworkers Memorial Bridge. After a two decade run, security conscious Port of Vancouver ended the restaurant's lease. Chef Eddy and a few others moved from The Cannery and began Pink Peppercorn Seafood House, taking with them many favourite recipes as well as the rustic maritime theme. An August visit to the Kingsway dining spot refreshed happy memories of The Cannery.
From the initial greeting to our departure, service was friendly and attentive, without being intrusive. To start, we enjoyed bread and the signature Lobster Oil dip with balsamic vinegar. She had mushroom and roasted garlic soup, I had lobster bisque. Both delicious. Her entree was Sablefish with a lemon butter sauce, mine was Salmon Wellington. Each came with asparagus and broccoli, perfectly cooked to tender crisp. Portions are huge so take-home containers are pretty routine. The menu is broad and suitable for most tastes. It's a family friendly restaurant more worthy of our support than outlets of the corporate chains that dominate Vancouver dining.

featured_reviews.review_id:
Old school seafood joint, and i mean that in the most complimentary manner. We loved it here, we had a professional waiter - a fellow who could read the table, make recommendations and have facility with the menu. It's a rare skill these days and is a lost art. I value old school anything so I feel this is a restaurant meant for people who know what they want. It's not an effete molecular cuisine restaurant or a fish and chip joint.  The portions are generous and the flavours are dynamic- if pepper, garlic and onion are your friends, you need to run here as soon as possible. We will
Return , we had the smoked sablefish and the salmon Wellington and wish I had an extra stomach to try the other dishes.

featured_reviews.review_id:
Wonderfully presented meals that will impress your eyes and belly!  The service is professional, engaging and seamless. The place was at full capacity yet our appetizers and entrees were served exceptionally fast. It's obvious the kitchen is run at a high standard. The seafood and vegetables taste like they were pulled from the ocean and garden that day. Notably the lobster bisque was rich and creamy while the mixed seafood pasta was loaded with clams,salmon, scallops and prawns. Definitely try the smokey, buttery Alaskan Cod as it is absolutely delicious. The trio of tartar was light refreshing and super tasty.
I have been here twice and both times I have left  feeling  like the meals were prepared by someone who loves you.

featured_reviews.review_id: Made an online purchase of 3 parrot perches.  Went to pick up and browse for other items.  The staff were helpful but I couldn't help feeling my presence was an inconvenience.  The poor review though is based on the fact that while I was paying for my items the salesperson started spraying a strong smelling cleaner on the counter right beside my items.  I asked her to keep it away and moved my items aside but she continued.  I should have stopped right there and returned the unprotected perches and toys.  Now I have them home and they do have a distinct smell.  I don't know what this product was but anyone who knows anything about birds knows that they are extremely vulnerable to toxins, inhaled or ingested. So I guess I'll be back tomorrow to return the 2 I didn't detag and I guess I'm out of luck on the other one and the two non returnable toys.  Pretty dumb move for a pet store.

featured_reviews.review_id: For three years this is been my go to for all of my pets needs. I admit that many times I arrive only to see products on the shelves not stocked however to avoid making my trip a complete waste of time to I pick up some treats or a sweater. The staff is not always knowledgable with information on items or when items will arrive however they love animals so much that I continue coming back and giving them another chance. In early December I noticed an event dedicated to getting your pets photo taken with Santa.  Excited for this day I ordered a special holiday sweater for my cat and rallied up 2 other friends with pets. On the day of we arrived with pets dressed in holiday ware only to learn that the event was cancelled that day because they couldn't find a Santa Claus costume. My latest negative experience is where I draw the line. The particular cat food Coco eats is always out of stock. I came in twice in one week only to find the shelf empty. The manager placed an order for me and promised me it would arrive on Thursday. I came on Saturday to see that empty shelf but surprisingly a case was behind the cashiers desk. When I inquired about the case I was told it was reserved for somebody else. I was told this by the same person (a manager) who assured me I would have the special ordered cat food waiting for me. It didn't make any sense why someone else was getting special treatment over Coco and I. It made me feel incredibly uncomfortable and unfairly treated. She had no suggestions or solutions to this issue. I don't think this location is properly trained and knowledgeable enough to run a successful business. Clearly the management needs to step it up first before this could happen. It's really sad that animals suffer the most because of this.

featured_reviews.review_id: Came here for the Alaskan King Crab dinner with my family this week and it was amazing and super reasonably priced. They pre-order the crab once you confirm your reservation and show you the crab before bringing it into the kitchen to cook (it was alive and flailing). The crab was perfectly cooked into 4 dishes. The legs and claws were steamed with garlic, the body fried with salt/pepper/shallot/garlic, seafood fried rice was baked into the shell, and residual meat/juice was used to poach some yuchoy. Everything was perfectly cooked and tasted fresh and delicious. Service was amazing too. You have to drive through some shady areas of Vancouver, but definitely work the trip. Highly recommend and would go back in a heartbeat.

featured_reviews.review_id:
Prepare yourself for a wild ride because Pelican Restaurant in East Hastings is not your average dining establishment. If you're an adventurous foodie seeking new taste experiences, this place is a hidden gem that deserves your attention. However, if you're looking for a visually stunning, Instagram-worthy ambiance, well, let's just say you won't find it here.

Upon entering Pelican Restaurant, you may be underwhelmed by its lackluster decor. But remember, it's the taste that matters, right? And boy, oh boy, did Pelican deliver in that department. Every dish we devoured was an explosion of flavors that made our taste buds dance happily.

We decided to visit Pelican for brunch, and it turned out to be an epic choice. Who needs pancakes and eggs benedict when you can have a unique culinary experience like no other? We knew we were in for something extraordinary when they opened their doors at 10 am.

The menu at Pelican is a delightful mishmash of creative concoctions that will challenge your preconceived notions of what a brunch should be. Expect the unexpected as you peruse through their intriguing selection. From out-of-this-world flavor combinations to random ingredients, Pelican dares to push the boundaries of culinary norms.

As we devoured each plate, we couldn't help but appreciate the boldness and creativity that went into the dishes. Pelican Restaurant is a playground for innovative flavors and unexpected pairings.

Sure, the decor might not be Insta-worthy, and the ambiance lacks pizzazz, but who needs that when the food is this extraordinary? Pelican is a haven for true food enthusiasts who are willing to step outside their comfort zones and embrace the weird and wonderful.

So, if you're a true gastronomic adventurer seeking a new experience of taste, make your way to Pelican Restaurant in East Hastings. Come with an open mind, and an empty stomach, and prepare to have your taste buds blown away. Trust me, it's a brunch you won't soon forget.

featured_reviews.review_id: Decent food at decent prices with generous portions. They usually "comp" us the baked tapioca pudding dessert, which I find is a nice touch at the end of our multi-course family meal. The fried black cod in Maggie sauce was a favourite as was the salted paper-wrapped roasted crispy chicken.  Pea shoots in superior broth with roasted garlic was also a good veggie dish.  The live seafood prices were fair and I enjoyed the fresh crab in green onion and ginger sauce which was very meaty.  We've been coming here regularly with my extended family for a long time due to its consistency, fair prices, and decent size dishes.

featured_reviews.review_id:
Put in an online order for a whole roast duck a day before. Showed up 20 mins after the pickup time and the staff member had no idea what I was talking about. After making me wait a while, they had their kitchen put my order together anew. I will give them kudos for managing to get me my food in 5-10 minutes, but this should've never been the case. When I opened up my order at home, the duck was already sliced up (which is great), but they definitely gave me only half the bird. I was already late for dinner, I called the restaurant after my family had our meal. The guy on the phone said they did indeed give me the whole duck, and the smaller serving is because ducks nowadays are smaller in size. He made sure to tell me that there were two legs and two wings, which I couldn't confirm, since I had called the restaurant after my family had already eaten the dish for dinner. However, as a Chinese person, I have grown up eating many a duck and I know what a whole vs half duck looks like. This barely filled the bottom of their round takeout container. I know that with Peking Duck orders, restaurants will often take part of the duck meat to make lettuce wraps to be served alongside sliced pieces, but this is not what I had ordered, nor did I get any bonus lettuce wraps - my order was one WHOLE duck. If they did give me two wings and legs, my best guess is that they kept the bulk of the duck to make lettuce wraps for some other customer. On top of that, the restaurant claims to give you 15% off for takeout orders, which was also a lie.

Save your money and go somewhere else. Don't get ripped off by this dishonest business.

Or at least be prepared to be charged $45 for a whole quail-sized duck.

There are some parking spots in the street beside as well as at the back of building if you can't park in Kingsway right in front of the restaurant.

featured_reviews.review_id:
WORST CUSTOMER SERVICE!

When they serve food such as soup or dessert, they generally come and pour for you or would cut the dessert accordingly in slices. The server ended up just "throwing" the food into the bowl or plates, leaving a mess on the table, walking away.

The dessert came, not looking like what it was supposed to be, the tapioca pudding. It was very bland (no taste), liquidy (it shouldn't be), and the crust was burnt and dry. We mentioned to the server that this wasn't right and he just quickly walked away and just responded "ah". Then he came and gave us the bill. We were also missing another dessert that was part of the menu and they still never gave it even when they confirmed with us that they are bringing both.

The crab we ordered also were missing the claws... did the owner or server eat it?

Food wasn't good, service was terrible, also not clean as well (spiders crawling around vents and walls), and the chairs aren't sturdy.

featured_reviews.review_id:
We went here for the first time today and I felt so disappointed. I think it will also be my last time coming here because I was actually not satisfied with the food. First of all it was so salty. I don't know what you did to my king crab legs sea food boil but the sauce was extremely salty to the point where I had to order a different food which was the clams and mussels just to compare if the sauce was really supposed to be like that. When I tasted the cajun sauce of the mussel and clam it was surprisingly fine (better than the cajun sauce of the king crab). I was wondering why this happened but I didn't bother being a Karen because there were too many people and I felt ashamed to even ask seeing how busy it was today. Please look into your salt pouring/measuring because imagine going to sea and drinking the salty water, that is what the sauce tasted like.
For having to pay $150 I must say it is not worth it. Great trial and error though. Try at your own risk.

featured_reviews.review_id:
We went with a high expectations because of the reviews. I actually invited my friends travelled to North Vancouver for a good evening at this place.

Unfortunately, we hit a very bumpy ride.

The patio is so right next to the road, tightly, that if you stretched at the wrong timing, a bus will hit your arms.
When asked for a sample for the beer on tap, the waitress brought it with a glass that has a crack on top and goes whole the way to almost bottom. I hesitated a bit but finished it carefully because I and my friends were in a nice conversation so I didn't want to be disrupted. When I reminded the waitress this issue, she was like 'oh I didn't see this when I brought it.' I was filled with question marks in my head because it's not possible to miss it.

To start with, we ordered the oysters  that we were excited about. TBH, they did not taste too fresh to me, but my friend thinks that it's not bad. However, we both agreed that the oysters are very small, like smaller than the spoon  for them.
We also ordered the seafood tower, another thing that we are excited about. It looks great and tastes great as well. But all items are significantly smaller than other places.

Additionally, a dish with tuna came with a piece of dirty plastic wrap mixed in it. it's really gross. But when we told the waitress, she took it away immediately. She came back in a few mins and said 'okay, we took it out of your bill.' and left. We feel like she did not take food safety seriously and is very used to this issue.

We felt unsafe to eat more at this moment.

It was too late to go somwhere else, so we stayed but drank only water from this point. In the end of the day, we spent almost $200 for three people and I ended up heating my leftover when got home.

Very embarrassed from inviting my friend came all the way to North Van for a night like this.

In sum, for the taste and the drinks, it's quite good. But I am concerned about the food quality and safety there.
#EatAtYourOwnRisk

featured_reviews.response_from_owner_text:
Dev,

We sincerely apologize for falling short of meeting your expectations, and we appreciate you bringing these concerns to our attention.

Firstly, we want to emphasize that our patio dining area fully complies with the safety rules and regulations set by the City of North Vancouver. We have not encountered any issues regarding its proximity to the road, and the safety and comfort of our guests are our top priorities.

Regarding the plastic wrap found in your tuna dish, we take full responsibility for the oversight on our part, and we deeply apologize for any discomfort caused. Furthermore, we would like to clarify that the plastic wrap was not dirty but rather the protective wrap we use to wrap the tuna before cutting it. However, we understand that it should not have been present in the final dish, and we removed it from your bill upon notification.

The immediate action taken by our server reflects our commitment to addressing any issues promptly. We regret if her response left you with the impression that food safety was not taken seriously. Rest assured, we continuously train our staff to uphold the highest standards of food safety, and incidents like this are not common in our restaurant.

Regarding the oysters, we typically offer smaller-sized oysters as they are favored by many of our regular patrons. However, we also have a premium option available, and the size of the oysters can vary depending on our supplier.

Lastly, the seafood towel you ordered was advertised as a towel for two people to share, and we understand that it may not have seemed enough to share between the three of you.

Thank you for acknowledging the good taste and drinks at our restaurant. We strive to maintain the quality of our offerings while continuously improving our food quality and safety measures to provide an exceptional dining experience.

We appreciate your feedback, and we will use it to make the necessary improvements.

featured_reviews.review_id:
Another sure winner when dining in North Vancouver, the Fishworks is in a trendy neighborhood with ample parking nearby and a nice view down the street. Service is fast and very friendly, the menu if interesting and varied. Happy Hour oysters are 1.50 each, so we had a dozen. Fresh and delicious. My wife had the special, pan fried Halibut in a roasted red pepper sauce which was delicious, perfectly prepared. I had the Paella with prawns, mussels and clams, it was delicious.
Atmosphere is cozy and warm, altogether a delightful experience.
Would highly recommended.

featured_reviews.review_id:
Great evening at this local seafood gem.  We had the soup of the day which was a lovely mix of sweet potatoes, pear and spinach ... then our calamari starter which was so fresh and crispy served with a lemon wedge and hot sauce.  For our mains we ordered the Salmon Wellington and Paella both of which were a hit and we really enjoyed the complexity of flavours and textures.  Our server was knowledgeable and attentive.  However we felt quite rushed at the end by another staff who might have been our hostess when we first walked in.  She wanted to take our plates away and waited while I finished my last bite!
Would definitely recommend this place for a nice evening of dining out.  A great location and buzzing with life atmosphere and dim lighting ... some live jazz music would have made it a perfect evening.

featured_reviews.review_id: Local, multigenerational family run business. Longliner Seafoods never disappoints. I've been coming here for a few years now for my seafood, and could never go anywhere else - it is always super fresh, and super delicious. Their organic spring salmon is some of the best I've ever had (highly recommend), and their smoked salmon selection is fantastic. I always go for the peppered nuggets (super moist and flavourful), the double smoked, and the cold smoked spring - they're the only people I've seen who cold smoke spring salmon! The service is always wonderful and they often go above and beyond. It's a bit pricey, however it's expected for the quality and location. I have and will continue recommending this place!

featured_reviews.review_id:
We ordered the lobster roll and the mussels and fries.

The lobster roll was good and had an unexpected flavour, maybe fennel or something? I enjoyed it and it was reasonably priced for what it was.

The mussels were a bit slimy so I wasn't too impressed with those. The white wine and garlic sauce also tasted a bit like burnt garlic and seemed like it could have been cooked down a bit longer as it was really watery. Fries were really good, though.

Service was really casuals. Just more off a drop-off thing, which is fine. Nice view.

featured_reviews.review_id:

featured_reviews.review_id:
By far one of my favourite place to go in Vancouver! Every time we go to Vancouver we make sure we stop by the Rodney oyster's house in Yaletown.
From fresh oysters to one of the best service I've had in a restaurant, this is definitely a place you need to try.
Every single plate was perfect and came super fast, we got the crab cakes, garlic shrimps, shrimp cocktail, clams, mussels and obviously oysters. Everything was so fresh and the oysters come with a lot of different choices of sauces for you to choose from.
Very clean restaurant and very cute ambiance for a date, a dinner with friends or even to just go by yourself !
The staff working there has one of the best service I've seen in years, they are really on point and so friendly and nice, this is one of the reasons we always go back there, we just love the ambiance and service so much, a lot of place should take exemple of this place !
We've been served by Mackenzie and sadly I don't forget the name of the other employees that took care of us but it isn't the last time they will see us in the establishment!
IF YOU LOVE SEAFOOD AND GOOD VIBES YOU NEED TO TRY THIS PLACE !

featured_reviews.review_id:
I'm very impressed with the quality of Rodney's Oyster House. Great food and service, a fun place to be in, top class all around.

We found that it is important to reserve a table, even in the middle of the week (it was summer, too, so that might add a bit).

The waiter was great, the hot sauce defection was wonderful, and the choices in oyster types was unexpected and fantastic to have. We dove right in, so if you see the picture I took you can tell that a lot of the oysters had already been eaten by the time I got my camera out.

You know, you go away from raw oysters for a while and you start thinking, "I'm kind of ok without them," or "Did I really eat those things?" But then you get taken to Rodney's and you relearn that oysters are amazing things to eat.

Tried one of each of the 8 different oysters that were available. They were all so good although I was gravitating towards the briny ones. Sean executed them well on the plate by placing them in the order as the menu so we'd know which variety we were eating.

The fresh prawn cocktail were huge and meaty and the fried oyster were so crunchy and delicious. Fries were perfectly crunchy.

I love the cozy environment and the window seat is great for eating and people watching. I will definitely be back.  Highly recommend.

Coziest little oyster bar ever! I don't know if it seats more than a dozen people, but I am glad I was one of them last week. Top class fresh oysters, usually 6-7 varieties to choose from.
The raw shucked are outstanding - the shucker is a master. We had 2 dozen raw and each was a work of shucking art - each oyster perfectly separated from its shell, undamaged in any way. And with the liquor intact. That is some skill. Hat's off! Oh, and the homemade chili-vodka condiment? Inspired!

The fried oysters were big meaty west coasters, perfectly crispy, juicy.

I want to go back with a bigger group, so we can try them all.
Big thanks to the owners - such nice people

The raw shucked are outstanding - the shucker is a master. We had 2 dozen raw and each was a work of shucking art - each oyster perfectly separated from its shell, undamaged in any way. And with the liquor intact. That is some skill. Hat's off! Oh, and the homemade chili-vodka condiment? Inspired!

The fried oysters were big meaty west coasters, perfectly crispy, juicy.

I want to go back with a bigger group, so we can try them all.
Big thanks to the owners - such nice people

featured_reviews.review_id: Small oyster bar in Chinatown. Had variety of oysters from BC, PEI and elsewhere. The happy hour oyster for 2.50 each was a bit bland and unexciting. The favorite was the Gorge Inlet which was larger in size and tastier than the other options. The fried oyster was really good too. Would rate it higher if was bit cheaper in prices.

featured_reviews.review_id:
Newer restaurant that replaced Peaceful restaurant that was there prior. The GOOD: place was busy for a Sat night at 8pm so that's a good sign. Didn't wait long for a table for 2. Pleasantly surprised at the preset 2x combo meats + main + soup + 2 bowls of white rice for $56. So we ordered BBQ duck + pork, main was green beans w minced pork & soup of the day.

The MEH: menu should have spelled out that the combo soup is the soup of the day; no choosing. We asked for hot n sour, but the server brought the daily soup instead. When asked why, she then said the combo soup has to be daily soup.

I found the BBQ pork and duck very tasty and not too oily. The green beans w minced pork were perfectly crispy but not too deep-fried. Again, very tasty. Didn't care for the daily soup, as it's just a thin broth w few veggies + few pieces of meat. Would have preferred the hot n sour 

Final bill w tax was just under $60.

featured_reviews.review_id:
Cantonese BBQ Seafood opened up in the former Peaceful location on Kingsway. The little mini mall has a busy parking lot but you can usually find street parking (both free and paid).

We've been here a few times to grab a quick bbq lunch combo. But we finally visited for dine-in recently. In addition to their bbq service, they have a full Chinese seafood menu offering.

We ordered the 3 item bbq combo (you pick and choose which bbq items you want but we opted for the roast pork, bbq, and soya sauce chicken). While the bbq price is higher than the lunch combos, you get more meat. Not a bad price when you consider how much the price of bbq duck has gone up lately. The duck was good... meaty and juicy. Roast pork has nice crispy skin. A welcome addition to the area for bbq.

Pea tips were good too. And I like that we received complimentary soup to start and green bean soup for dessert.

Really want to come back here and try some of their seafood combos.

Update: We did return in October to try a dinner combo with a 2lb lobster sticky rice with 2 bbq items plus 1 other dish for $118 (we picked the sole fillets with veggies). We also added the Taiwanese cauliflower with lap cheung and bacon. Again, you get complimentary soup and dessert. Bbq items were as good as before.

featured_reviews.review_id:
Absolutely disgusting. The Shao Rou  (roasted pork) was not flavourful but the Cha Shao  (bbq pork) was just fat and sugar, their Xian Guo Gu Lu Rou  (fresh fruit sweet and sour pork) tasted off with a subtle funny flavour and mass-produced feeling texture, and anything but "Xian " (fresh), Hei Jiao Niu Liu  (black pepper beef) was thick-cut cheap beef doused with baking soda and I could barely chew through it. Even the white rice was gummy.
However, their Jiao Yan Dou Fu  (salt and pepper tofu) was quite nice, texture was dense with a crispy and salty shell to contrast with the flavourless internals. I also enjoyed the soup at the beginning, though a little salty, and abhorred the mung bean Tang Shui  (dessert water) brought out at the end.

R u kidding?
I suspected they recently changed their owner. I used to be a loyal client for over 5years. Recenlty notice all old staffs disappeared...all 'new faces".
Will not go back and suggest whoever view this comment not going there.

featured_reviews.review_id:
Aquariums West is an aquatic paradise right in the heart of Vancouver. I was immediately captivated by the sheer variety of plants available - from lush greens to vibrant reds, they had a wide selection that were visually stunning. The knowledge and guidance provided by the staff made it easy to select the perfect plants for my aquarium.

One of the most delightful discoveries during my visit was the adorable cherry shrimp. These little creatures added an unexpected charm to the store. The staff's expertise in caring for these small invertebrates was evident, and their health and vivacity were a testament to the store's commitment to quality and care for all its inhabitants.

The store itself is a treasure trove for any aquatic enthusiast. Beyond the vibrant flora and charming shrimp, Aquariums West boasts an impressive array of supplies and fish species. The attention to detail in maintaining the tanks and the quality of the aquatic life on offer truly sets this place apart.

Whether you're a seasoned aquarist or a newcomer to the hobby, Aquariums West is an absolute must-visit. The diversity, quality, and expert guidance make it a top destination for all things aquatic. I left not just with new additions for my tank but also with a wealth of knowledge. Kudos to Aquariums West for providing such a wonderful experience.

featured_reviews.review_id:
Honestly this is the best (and only?) good Aquarium store in the city. Always super knowledgeable & helpful staff regarding reptiles and fish. Aquarium equipment and supplies. A Great selection of water plants.
They also sell rodents, guinea pigs and chinchillas too!

Pretty much bought everything for our tank from this store over the past 15 years. Except our actual tank which was from the 80s.

Just a heads up side note;

It can be a little uptight with the on-going covid restrictions and how you enter and leave the store can be a bit uncomfortable and off-putting.

You have to leave your backpack behind the counter and wait behind a rope before being allowed entry.
This is understandable in our city of Vancouver where shoplifting & addiction is rampant unfortunately. This store is way too nice to let any scumbags in. I get it.

featured_reviews.review_id:
I've finally made it to this place after a long desire to come here.  The lack of parking and location make it hard to visit.

The store is clean and tidy.  However I am thrilled about how clean their tanks are.  Also they seem to specialize in planted tanks.  Fish are also quite unique.

We were asked if we needed help twice so we were looked after well.  The prices are decent and we noticed other stores upping the cost of basic fish like neon tetras.  I won't complain about the cost here because everything costs more in this day in age..  Plus rental space downtown is not cheap.

featured_reviews.review_id: Let me start by saying that honestly, the seafood here is great and fresh, and you can find stuff you don't find elsewhere and prices are reasonable, BUT don't expect anything else. They only do Cash which is very very annoying as you have to run bring cash and come back, they don't speak a single word in English so it's very very hard to communicate with them we had to translate through Google and show them what we needed at some point.  The lady that works here is very sweet, and she tries, but the males are very rude, and they yell a lot. My friend went to bring cash before we knew the total price so we were short of 50$ and said we will go bring more hold on but the guy started screaming in Chinese and just dropped some of the stuff we brought back to the tanks and kept only the food we had the cash for at the moment (our order was 200$, for this amount i expect a better treatment at least! Plus, we were about to go bring more cash!!) But they didn't understand us. We didn't understand them it's just a mess! I was annoyed that i couldn't get the rest of the stuff i wanted, and after that , I was not willing to go bring more money and spend it here! Also, if a Chinese customer comes even after you, they get to pass you and pay first even if you're standing there first, so just expect that.

featured_reviews.review_id: My husband and I spent a weekend in Seattle and then traveled by train to Vancouver. We went straight from the train station to the restaurant and had the best meal of our trip so far. The crab baguette was fantastic. Crusty yet soft baguette with an explosion of flavors. The fennel slaw added an amazing crunch and flavor. We also had the salmonito wrap. Fresh and fantastic - the salmon was cut right then and there to make our wrap. The fries were excellent too and we dipped them in the housemade tartar sauce. The staff was incredible and made sure we were happy with our food. I don't often leave reviews but this was too good not to note. Take the time to visit this slightly out of the way spot. You won't be disappointed. I'm hoping my first visit to Vancouver won't be my last because I'll be dreaming of this food for awhile.

featured_reviews.review_id: After a long and rewarding stroll from downtown to the Bloedel conservatory, I enjoyed one of the best , if not the best, fish and chips of my life. I was recommended to try the halibut and, oh boy! Heavenly, not oily at all, crispy and light, seasoned to perfection. A generous serving of fish on a bed of fantastic fries, coleslaw and tartar dip. Super friendly staff, cool and laidback interior, with some seating by the window. Really really recommended, as they focus on local, seasonal and sustainable seafood. Really awesome!

featured_reviews.review_id:
Its usually halibut, salmon, or cod managed to veer off my typical menu choices and explore the Arctic Char for my Fish and Chips order.

From the onset, the service representative demonstrated a commendable level of hospitality and eagerness to cater to this unique request since it was not on the menu that was very nice of them.

Now, onto the main event - the Arctic Char Fish and Chips. To say it was superb would be an understatement. The perfectly fried Arctic Char exceeded all my expectations. It was succulent and full of flavour, pairing harmoniously with the crispy chips. This dish struck a perfect balance between the delicate fish and the satisfyingly crunchy chips. Its like a perfect balance between trout and salmon in taste.

This was, without a doubt, the best Arctic Char Fish and Chips I have ever had in Canada. Their tartar sauce is also to die for they now sell it in mason jars great choice.

Rating: 5/5 Stars

featured_reviews.review_id:
Pricy for what you get compared to other restaurants.
Seafood Pasta for $37 had 2 medium sized scallops, 4 smaller shrimp, 10 assorted shelled clams/mussels. Sauce was over spiced (not hot) and missing a fresh component that could have balanced it out a bit. Scallop pasta dish for $36 with 5 medium sized scallops and a bland cream sauce (missing fresh or acidic component or something).
Bam Bam Honey shrimp was good but the shrimp were smaller than expected for $22 but there was a decent amount of them.
Hostess was good but serving staff was just alright - don't go here if you aren't drinking as you won't get service as good as other tables that are. It is was very obvious and made didn't improve the atmosphere. It is a bit loud when the places fills up but you can still hear your dinner companions.
However they do have a great wine and beer menu for those who do partake.
The restaurant was clean and well staffed. Should have reservations if not going during happy hour (which is before 6).
Table had wood splinters coming off but the tables were spacious enough for multiple plates and they can accommodate larger groups.

featured_reviews.review_id: My family was visiting Vancouver from Montreal last week, and was introduced by our friend to Seafood City because it sells fresh fish straight from Japan.  We were looking for sashimi grade fish, particularly Hamachi.  They don't have it at the time, but they introduced Shima Aji, which was pretty close to what we were looking for, and we were glad to follow their recommendation.  We also purchased  Bluefin tuna, and of course the toro was very fresh.  We were very happy with the quality of sashimi grade fish we got there, and will definitely visit the place again the next time we go to Vancouver.  Thank you Seafood City.

April's Aquarium has become a mecca for the planted Aquarium hobby. I can't  say enough good things. They regularly order unique and interesting fish. Their team is surprisingly knowledgeable.

The experience has improved since the two locations merged. Having all the live stock in one location is convenient.

I've been very happy with aquarium coop products, and the wide selection of hardscape. They stand by their product warranties.

Lastly, April's aquarium treats their fish with great care. They score big points on quality. The fish they sell are well fed and healthier than I'm used too. I haven't had any issues with diseases. They are the only store I know of that quarantines all of their fish before selling it.

featured_reviews.review_id:
This is an incredible aquarium store, highly recommend!

Over the last few months I've been building a 55 gallon aquarium for my 21-year old Red Eared Slider. Every employee there is really knowledgeable about aquarium care. Although I wasn't there to buy fish, the principles are all pretty much the same for my turtle, and I was able to get all the necessary decorations, chemicals, and materials to make the perfect home for my turtle.

I also ordered my aquarium stand from them at a great price compared to other stores, and they hand-delivered it to me within the week! I felt particularly grateful for that, because I did not have the strength to carry that item myself, and I was already a bit stressed about that. They took the worry right out of my hands. Not to mention...it was free!

I also had one of the employees teach me about improving the flora in my aquarium, and advised me on some good decorations that would not just be pretty, but support the health of the tank. Since I've done the recommendations, my tank is healthier than it has ever been, and it requires less maintenance compared to before. Every time I go into the store I learn a bunch of new things!

I always enjoy going to April's Aquarium. Not just because it's fun to look at the fishes and browse the goods, but because the service is truly top notch. I highly recommend it for all your aquarium needs! Thank you!

featured_reviews.review_id:
In my opinion we need more Local Fish Stores (LFS). As a child growing up in the Lower Mainland the only fish stores I knew were LFS where the owners were hobbyist and knew about the fish with great advice. There are very few of those stores left and as far as my now decades in the hobby guides my understanding April's is great store. In the new location they are working hard to improve and things are only getting better. I often travel to Seattle and impressed by LFS like Aquarium Coop, Aquarium Zen and Sierra Pets and as far as I am concerned April's is as close to those experiences that you'll find locally.

As I work to add fish to my newest planted tanks April's was the go-to for variety and selection and reasonable price. I bought enough fish so that they were delivered to ... you can't get any better than that.

featured_reviews.review_id:
I visited North Vancouver District the first time just to try the food here. Honestly, they are best fish and chips I've ever had--better others I've had in Greater Vancouver!

The in-house tartar sauce was sooo delicious as well (can squeeze out as much as I want); it had a fresh, tarty dill taste.

The onion rings and oyster were good. And the tomato juice was tasty and refreshing.

The mushy peas, however, were not my cup of tea (it, to me, is like a coarse base puree that's just salted).

It was quite the satiating lunch; perfect for going to a hike trail afterward.  Moreover, I did not need to eat dinner.

As for the service, it's excellent. I liked the waitress' personality; she's chill and accommodating.

featured_reviews.review_id:
As I work close in the area this was a convenient stop for me to grab some Spot Prawns for the coveted Spot Prawn season here in Vancouver. It was after work, so I was lucky enough to catch Calvin the owner unloading a van full of Spot Prawns that were massive and still kicking.

We did he prawns sashimi style and a quick boil. These were some of the best prawns I've had even better than what I've had at sushi restaurants.

Debating if I need to go for round 2 of prawns tonight.

We did he prawns sashimi style and a quick boil. These were some of the best prawns I've had even better than what I've had at sushi restaurants.

Debating if I need to go for round 2 of prawns tonight.

featured_reviews.review_id:
I headed straight to The Lobster Man for lunch upon reaching Granville island market.

My wife and I ordered Signature and Connecticut lobster roll. I preferred the former while my wife preferred the latter. Both were so good.

It's not a restaurant but more of a takeout place with some outdoor seating. I love it as it serves great lobster rolls without much fanfare and sitting outdoors in a casual environment is such an enjoyment.

We visited the live seafood next door where we were keen to try the sea urchins. However, they don't cut the sea urchins for you so I decided it was too much hassle to cut it myself. It didn't look as delicious as ones I had in Hokkaido so am ok to give it a pass.

Don't miss out on the lobster rolls though.

featured_reviews.review_id:
Live lobster, crab, and oysters are often considered some of the best options for seafood enthusiasts for several reasons:

1. Freshness: Live seafood is the epitome of freshness. When you order live lobster, crab, or oysters, you can be confident that you're getting seafood at its peak quality and flavor.

2. Flavor: Live seafood tends to have a more delicate and succulent flavor compared to seafood that has been frozen or stored for an extended period. The natural sweetness of these creatures is best preserved when they are alive until just before cooking.

3. Texture: The texture of live lobster and crab is exceptional. When cooked properly, the meat is tender, juicy, and full of natural juices, making it a delightful dining experience. Oysters, on the other hand, are prized for their unique texture and briny, oceanic taste.

4. Interactive Dining: There's an interactive aspect to dining on live seafood. Preparing and cracking open a lobster or crab can be a fun and engaging experience, perfect for social gatherings and special occasions.

It's really fun dining experience here in lobster man.

Especially thank staff Sean.
He provided exceptional service. He was attentive, friendly, and knowledgeable.
Sean went above and beyond to ensure our dining experience was enjoyable.
We appreciated his recommendations and the way he made us feel well taken care of throughout the meal. Thank you, Sean, for making our visit special!"

featured_reviews.review_id:
A satisfying lunch experience here trying out the signature lobster and crab rolls.

The lobster filling was fresh and tasty on a brioche roll. A nice balance between the meat, dressing and bun.

My friend said that the crab roll was OK but a little to creamy (too much dressing)  to really taste the crab.

Both are served with very nice crinkle cut salted chips in a box that you can eat out of.

Not the cheapest lunch but decent value for money for the area.

Very few seats here and its not exactly an attractive part of Granville Island, however, there's lots of nice places with public picnic tables great views close by, by the marina, at the back of the market or by the sea wall.

If you choose the sea wall at the moment, you'll see lots of geese and goslings.

featured_reviews.review_id:
Fresh Ideas Start Here sells fresh and frozen sustainably caught seafood and the majority of their products are locally sourced. They have seafood that is raw and ready to cook as well as foods that have already been assembled and may just need a bit of time in the oven or on the stove before it's ready to eat. (eg. Crab Cakes,Truffle Spot Prawn Mac n Cheese)

To celebrate the launch of their fall seasonal menu, Fresh Ideas Start Here was offering a small bowl of complimentary seafood congee to the first 50 customers who came into their store and mentioned the word "halibut." We'd never tried this seafood congee before, but apparently it's a "cult favourite" so we went to the store right when it opened and managed to bring home some of this famed seafood congee.

Oh wow! This seafood congee exceeded my expectations. I totally understand now why it's a cult favourite. It was packed with seafood. They don't skimp on ingredients at this place. According to the stickers stuck onto our containers, a small congee is normally $6 and a large congee is normally $8. I would absolutely go back and pay to have this seafood congee again! I'm so happy that it's Fall now. With hot summer days leaving, and cooler weather arriving, we should definitely have a reason to go back for the seafood congee!

Service: Good
Parking: Plentiful and free
Location: 7515 Market Crossing #180, Burnaby
